  <description><![CDATA[<p>Owned and lovingly run by the Segl family, the Sportresort Alpenblick pairs modern alpine design with personal family-run service. You can expect good food in the restaurant and wine suggestions from their own sommeliers.</p>
<h2>Family Friendly</h2>
<p>Sportresort Alpenblick prides itself on being a family-run hotel and caters to other families and couples with an excellent level of service. The hotel runs a popular kids' club for ages 3-8 from Monday to Friday. They run a series of activities so you can enjoy the slopes or relax in the wellness area knowing the kids are well taken care of. There is also a rec room for older children with game consoles, air hockey, and darts.</p>
<h2>Ski Bus</h2>
<p>The hotel is located just outside of Zell am See and getting to the lifts and centre of town couldn't be easier, with a bus stop just in-front of the hotel. If you fancy some fresh air you can walk to the cobbled centre of town in 20 minutes, or the bus ride takes just a few minutes.</p>
<h2>Panorama Water World</h2>
<p>Health and wellness is a focus for the hotel and their large wellness area is fed by their very own Alpenblick spring. Enjoy snowy mountain views from the indoor and outdoor pool, warm up in one of the saunas, or deep cleanse in the amethyst steam bath.</p>]]></description>
